 call 23 Feb 2026"], "narrative": "This is a competitive, multi-vendor evaluation. Salesforce Competitors lists Coupa, GEP Worldwide, JAGGAER, and SAP Ariba, and Tony confirmed on 25 Mar he is evaluating '4-5 solution providers.' On 23 Feb he noted he 'just spoke to another provider offering something similar recently. They've given me a few... live demos... We've had some initial pricing from from them as well,' showing at least one rival is ahead of Zycus on pricing and demos. SAP Ariba is a latent strategic threat because AAK's global team is on SAP and plans a SAP migration in 3-5 years, which could favor a native SAP path. Zycus's wedge is the Microsoft Teams-embedded Merlin Intake guided-buying experience for low change-management overhead, plus the modular ability to start with eProcurement only and integrate with VAI now and SAP later. The named rival's identity on 23 Feb was not stated, so per-vendor ranking is partly inferred; the move is to confirm the competitive shortlist in the RFP."}, "identify_pain": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Avoma discovery call 03 Mar 2026", "Avoma intro call 23 Feb 2026"], "narrative": "Pain is specific and confirmed by the buyer. Tony Singleton (03 Mar 2026) described users finding items on the Grainger site, then manually re-keying requisitions into VAI with no system connection, layered email approvals, and an all-or-nothing dollar-threshold approval flow in the ERP: 'There's a lot of steps... It's horrible.' Rogue/maverick spend is a core pain: 'we have no way of kind of steering the business' to preferred suppliers (03 Mar). Spend data is only ~80% accurate because POs often lack part numbers or descriptions, blocking sub-category analysis (03 Mar). The pain owner is Tony's lean US procurement team, which risks becoming a bottleneck (his words, 03 Mar). This is a real, owned operational pain, though not yet costed."}, "paper_process": {"status": "gap", "sources": ["Avoma discovery call 03 Mar 2026", "Avoma eProcure